One of Nigeria’s pop acts and songwriter Gilbert Bassey aka Gillian Baci is optimistic his kind of songs can kill depression. In a recent chat, Gillian Baci hopes he can help people struggling with depression find their way out through his music.   Jaiye Kuti opens up on role in Ile Alayo series     Gbenga Adeyinka 1st, Derenle Edun, Iyabo Ojo billed for…     Asha Gangali returns with Miss You   According to the music act cum filmmaker, his songs give hope. He also stated that he prefers to be addressed as a pop artist from Nigeria, rather than a Nigerian pop artist, because, to him, he is a global artist. He recently released a new project with visuals entitled Sweet Serenity.